only half lying = 半真半假地说

They were okay. = 他们还行吧（含糊、不想评价）

went out of his way to tell me = 特意去告诉我

what sweet kids they are = 他们是多么乖的孩子（感叹句结构）

I kept looking at Daisy. = 我一直看着Daisy（keep doing 表持续）

rubbing her ear = 给她揉耳朵

flea-scratch shake = 挠痒后那种抖动（狗的动作）

he was the least nice = 他是最不友好的

maybe I'm getting them confused = 也许我把他们搞混了

brushed forward = （头发）往前梳

the kind of kid who's one way in front of grown-ups and another way in front of kids = 在大人面前一套，在孩子面前一套

Yeah, I guess. = 嗯，大概吧（不确定语气）

hate those = 讨厌那种人（those 指那类人）

What's the deal with your face? = 你脸怎么回事？（不礼貌表达）

Were you in a fire or something? = 你是被火烧过吗之类的？（or something 随口补充）

she was completely shocked = 她完全震惊了

He didn't say it in a mean way. = 他不是恶意地说的

He was just asking. = 他只是问问而已
